snippet.textDisplay:
Having a sip of coffee on an icy evening, looking at the fireworks of diwali from 10th floor, she took a sigh filled with emotions.. sadness bound her in her lonely apartment. Remembering the days she used to spent with her family makes her realise again the harshness of adulthood. Today wasn't a good day in her office.. she became late this morning because now there is no one to wake her up like the school days. The dark purple sky with shades of pink was looking as gloomy as her cheerless face as she was thinking about tomorrow.. again she'll become late, again her boss will scold her and again her dinner will get burnt.. and when she was about to go sleep.. her phone rang.. she smiled, took the call and one voice came out of the phone, "Did you eat my dear? I'm making your favourite pickles and will get it couriered." Having heard the voice, she whispered.. "So jaa re.. re mann"💛

Dear Coke studio Bharat.. thank you for keeping such soulful music alive in today's tough time. This song is healing medicine for many people who work out of their hometown. Thank you to Shreya and swanand ji and whole team.❤
